make SchemeRegistry friendlier for DI frameworksScheme's in SchemeRegistry are registered via 'register' method, but there is no way to pass it a set of schemes so those can be registered in one step. This way it can be externally configured and 'spring/guice friendly'... something like this is sufficient...

